===Etymology 2===
Short for {{term|if you please}}, an intransitive, ergative form taken from {{term||if it pleases you}},<ref name="dictionary" /><ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref> which replaced ''[[pray]]''.

====Alternative forms====
* {{qualifier|for the exaggerated way it is often pronounced as the expression of annoyance}} [[puh-lease]]

====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}

# Used to make a polite request.
#: '''''Please''', pass the bread.''
#: ''Would you '''please''' sign this form?''
#: ''Could you tell me the time, '''please'''?''
# Used as an affirmative to an offer.
#: —''May I help you?  —'''Please'''.''
# An expression of [[annoyance]] or [[impatience]].
#: ''Oh, '''please''', do we have to hear that again?''

